Okay, here's how to do it.

Set up an event listener for `bboxchange` ([example](http://docs.jquerygeo.com/geomap/geomapbbox.html)), and let your handler check for the zoom level. Use one of the following shapeStyle objects depending on the level:

```javascript
{ width: "10px", height: "10px", borderRadius: "10px" } // level <= 10
{ width: "20px", height: "20px", borderRadius: "20px" } // level > 10
```

Pass the appropriate shape style into this function:

```javascript
function updateShapeStyle(shapeStyle) {
  var services = [$("#allFeaturesService"), $("#searchResultsService")];
  for (var i in services) {
    var service = services[i];
    service.geomap("option", "shapeStyle", shapeStyle);
  }
}
```

We may want to check the existing zoom and/or shapeStyle before setting the new one, so that we're not updating it on every zoom and pan.

A couple things to clean up:

1. getURLParams is still in job-advancedsearch.js, remove it
2. the code in shared.js is actually doing something (assigning a value to .previous-input), it should only define the getURLParams, not call it
3. in order to succesfully call the one in shared.js from job-advancedsearch.js, we will have to break it out of the "ready" function wrapper and make it more of a module like MapTip, e.g., replace:

    #!javascript
    $(function () {
      function getURLParams() {
        ...stuff...
      }
    });

with something like:

    #!javascript
    var OLM = (function (olm) {
      "use strict";
      olm.getURLParams = function () {

      ...stuff...
      };

      return olm;
    })(OLM || {});

Then in other .js files, we can call it like this: OLM.getURLParams();

You will need to add a second argument to the Details action in the Plan controller named view. Use the Details action in the Job controller for a guide, e.g., you will need to wrap the current HTML in the view in a @if != map block like this

```
  @if (ViewBag.view != "map")
  {
    <!-- current html -->
  } else {
    <!-- map html -->
  }
```

