Place disclaimer text throughout the site on the various image pages.

* RelatedImages/Details
* RelatedDocuments/Details
* Home/Images

Place the disclaimer below the image preview, or below the grid of images.

Instead of copying the same HTML around, create an HTML helper which returns a div like so:

```csharp
public MvcHtml ImageDisclaimer(this HtmlHelper htmlHelper)
{
  return MvcHtml.Create("<div class='image-disclaimer'>blah blah...</div>");
}
```

Then place the helper on the page with `@Html.ImageDisclaimer()`.

Make some adjustments to the styling of the site name, so that it's vertically centered with the buttons a bit bolder.

Here's some styling that should achieve that, but feel free to tweak it.

```css
#mobile .navbar-inner .brand {
  ...
  font-size: 1.8em;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding-top: .5em;
  padding-bottom: 0;
}
```

similar to how Job/Details has a DATA | MAP toggle, add an IMAGE | MAP toggle box to Plan/Details.

Only show this toggle if the plan:

1. has a Scan and
2. the scan has a GeoReferencedDate

The check in the .cshtml file is similar to how we're listing plans in Job/Details:



```
#!cs
 @{
   var scan = model.Scans.FirstOrDefault();
   if (scan != null && scan.GeoReferencedDate != null) {
     // show view toggle
   }
 }
```

this simple view will have search input for *both* job search & plan search but two different "go" buttons.

the page will not actually do anything except forward the input to either Job/AdvancedSearch or Plan/AdvancedSearch depending on which "go" button is clicked (or in which form the Enter key was pressed)

Please check out the new layout style of the Job/AdvancedSearch view (it doesn't use absolute positioning but rather display:inline-block + min-height). You can re-use your avSearchPnl & avResultsPnl classes. The new Index/AdvancedSearch view must define a couple ViewBag params like Job/AdvancedSearch (at the top):


```
#!C#

@{
  ViewBag.Title = "AdvancedSearch";
  ViewBag.ViewClass = "static-scroll";
}
```

make sure the aerial basemap service objects have the property:

style: { visibility: "hidden" }

when they're created.
